2. **A VIE to GAL**: Moving the army from Vienna to Galicia is another aggressive expansion move. Galicia is unoccupied, and this move will allow Austria to exert influence in Eastern Europe. It also positions Austria to potentially support future moves into Warsaw or to defend against Russian advances.

